The Vice President, Mike Pence, and the First Lady, Melania Trump, hosted the 2017 White House Picnic in the Park for members of the House of Representatives and the United States Senate. Pence expressed gratitude to the leadership from both parties and thanked all the men and women serving in Congress. He emphasized that the picnic is a bipartisan tradition that allows families to come together and leave politics outside the gate. President Donald Trump also spoke at the picnic, expressing his appreciation for the friendships he has developed with politicians. He mentioned Congressman Steve Scalise, who was injured in a shooting, and thanked the Capitol Police and members of Congress for their bravery during the incident. Trump hoped for unity and cooperation between Republicans and Democrats, stating that it would benefit the country. He concluded by thanking everyone for attending and wishing them a pleasant evening.